cially since the current build includes that. It appears to be a JVM argument rather than just an environment or system property. So, that's something to keep in mind while troubleshooting!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating test setup requirements**\\n\\nThe user is asking about setting up tests beyond the normal generated scaffold for meaningful coverage. The current test scaffold in build.gradle includes jvmArgs, but generated tests might not. I should research if \\\"local Gradle and Native image authoritative.\\\" It seems the Forge workflow may use the existing setup. If a test touches DnsSettings, then add-exports might be necessary, but I'm unsure about its requirement for meaningful coverage. I need to clarify if environment properties should be set.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing test setup and dependencies**\\n\\nI'm reviewing guidance regarding environment variables and system properties for test code setup. The JVM --add-exports might be necessary, but there's no clear need for general coverage unless testing DNS internals. I wonder if I need to mention risks when guidance is unclear. I should inspect artifact reference.conf for potential dynamic loading. The Java run failure comes from Scala compilation, but I need to check if TypedActor is moved or deprecated and potentially look for a separate pekko-typed-actor artifact. Searching Maven might be essential here!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_eR6zNsncRiNwwJY8kNH6DgvW|fc_0b85ddc32a9e113a016a40a09033d0819096864a384d1aeb98", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request, json, urllib.parse\nq='g:\"org.apache.pekko\" AND TypedActor AND v:\"2.0.0-M1\"'\nurl='https://search.maven.org/solrsearch/select?' + urllib.parse.urlencode({'q':q,'rows':'20','wt':'json'})\nprint(url)\ntry:\n data=json.load(urllib.request.urlopen(url, timeout=20))\n print(json.dumps(data.get('response',{}).get('docs',[])[:10], indent=2))\nexcept Excep